.\" ###### Setup ############################################################
.Dd May 22, 2026
.Dt gs\-clothify 1
.Os gs\-clothify
.\" ###### Name #############################################################
.Sh NAME
.Nm gs\-clothify
.Nd applies the GIMP Script\-Fu "Clothify" filter on an image
.\" ###### Synopsis #########################################################
.\" Manpage syntax help:
.\" https://forums.freebsd.org/threads/howto-create-a-manpage-from-scratch.13200/
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm gs\-clothify Ar input\_filename Ar output\_filename
.br
.Op Fl X Ar value | Fl Fl blur\-x Ar value
.br
.Op Fl Y Ar value | Fl Fl blur\-y Ar value
.br
.Op Fl A Ar bearing | Fl Fl azimuth Ar bearing
.br
.Op Fl E Ar bearing | Fl Fl elevation Ar bearing
.br
.Op Fl D Ar depth | Fl Fl depth Ar depth
.br
.Op Fl q | Fl Fl quiet
.Op Fl w | Fl Fl verbose
.Nm gs\-clothify
.Op Fl h | Fl Fl help
.Nm gs\-clothify
.Op Fl v | Fl Fl version
.\" ###### Description ######################################################
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm gs\-clothify
runs GIMP to load an image, applies the GIMP Script\-Fu "Clothify" filter
(details:
.Lk https://docs.gimp.org/3.0/en/script\-fu\-clothify.html "GIMP Script\-Fu Clothify" ) ,
and stores the result into an output file.
.Pp
.\" ###### Arguments ########################################################
.Sh ARGUMENTS
The following options are available:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Ar input\_filename
The input image. Any format supported by GIMP can be used. The format will be detected automatically.
.It Ar output\_filename
The name for the output image to be written. Any format supported by GIMP can be used. The format will be detected by the provided file name extension (e.g. .jpeg, .png, .webp, .pdf, ...). An existing output file will be overwritten.
.It Fl X Ar value | Fl Fl blur\-x Ar value
Sets the blur X parameter for the "Clothify" filter. Range: 3\-100. Default: 3.
.It Fl Y Ar value | Fl Fl blur\-y Ar value
Sets the blur Y parameter for the "Clothify" filter. Range: 3\-100. Default: 3.
.It Fl A Ar bearing | Fl Fl azimuth Ar bearing
Sets the azimuth parameter for the "Clothify" filter. Range: 0.0\-360.0. Default: 135.0.
.It Fl E Ar bearing | Fl Fl elevation Ar bearing
Sets the elevation parameter for the "Clothify" filter. Range: 0.5\-90.0. Default: 45.0.
.It Fl D Ar depth | Fl Fl depth Ar depth
Sets the depth parameter for the "Clothify" filter. Range: 1\-65. Default: 5.
.It Fl q | Fl Fl quiet
Quiet mode: suppress GIMP console output. This is the default.
.It Fl w | Fl Fl verbose
Verbose mode: print GIMP console output and processing details.
.It Fl h | Fl Fl help
Prints the program's command\-line parameters and exits.
.It Fl v | Fl Fl version
Prints the program version and exits.
.El
.\" ###### Exit status ######################################################
.Sh EXIT STATUS
The
.Nm
tool exits with 0 on success, and >0 in case of an error.
.\" ###### Examples #########################################################
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It gs\-clothify Bergen.jpeg Bergen\-Clothify.jpeg
.It gs\-clothify Bergen.jpeg Bergen\-Clothify\-with\-Border8.jpeg \-\-depth 8 \-\-verbose
.It gs\-clothify Bergen.jpeg Bergen\-Clothify\-with\-Depth5.jpeg \-D 5
.It gs\-clothify \-\-help
.It gs\-clothify \-h
.It gs\-clothify \-\-version
.It gs\-clothify \-v
.El
